Usage:
  install.bat component_name oracle_home_path oracle_home_name [install_dependents] [machine_wide_configuration] [tns_admin_location]

Example:
  install.bat all     c:\oracle myhome true
  (install all components and their dependencies)

  install.bat odp.net2  c:\oracle myhome true
  (install ODP.NET 2, Unmanaged Driver and its dependent components)

  install.bat odp.net4    c:\oracle myhome true true c:\tns
  (install and configure ODP.NET 4, Unmanaged Driver at the machine level, set TNS_ADMIN to c:\tns)

  install.bat odpm    c:\oracle myhome
  (install ODP.NET Managed Provider, do not configure at machine level)

  install.bat oramts  c:\oracle myhome true
  (install ORAMTS and its dependent components)

  install.bat asp.net2  c:\oracle myhome true
  (install ASP.NET Providers 2 and its dependent components)

  install.bat asp.net4  c:\oracle myhome true
  (install ASP.NET Providers 4 and its dependent components)

  install.bat oledb     c:\oracle myhome true
  (install OraOLEDB and its dependent components)

  install.bat oledbolap c:\oracle myhome true
  (install OraOLEDB OLAP and its dependent components)

  install.bat basic   c:\oracle myhome false
  (install Oracle Instant Client)

NOTE:
- By default, install_dependents=true and machine_wide_configuration=false.
- machine_wide_configuration only applies to odp.net4 and odpm components.
- In order to specify tns_admin_location, machine_wide_configuration and install_dependents have to be specified.

